body_html:
enqueue_data, which already turns numpy arrays and pandas DataFrames into TensorFlow queues, is possibly a good entry point for this functionality: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/learn/python/learn/dataframe/queues/feeding_functions.py

(It's already serves some use uses in-between feed_dict and tf.train.Example protos)

body:
`enqueue_data`, which already turns numpy arrays and pandas DataFrames into TensorFlow queues, is possibly a good entry point for this functionality: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/learn/python/learn/dataframe/queues/feeding_functions.py

(It's already serves some use uses in-between `feed_dict` and `tf.train.Example` protos)
